 Mount Ayliff - Police in Mount Ayliff have appealed to the public for assistance with information that can help them solve a homicide case which occurred at Singeni Locality in Mount Ayliff on Monday night. "It is alleged that a 33-year-old male, Zolile Nomaqaqa, was found dead with a stab wound in his upper body and eyes gorged out," described police spokesperson, W/O ZIlungile Nkamba. "The deceased was last seen in another house at Singeni locality where there were preparations of circumcision. "He was found dead the next morning. The circumstances of murder are not yet developed." W/O Nkamba said that an arrest is imminent. SAPS Cluster Commander for the area, Brigadier Mtutuzeli Mtukushe, condemned this gruesome murder. "He extended words of condolences to the deceased's family," said W/O Nkamba. "Brig Mtukushe requested the public to furnish information to police for swift arrest of the suspect/s. Information will be treated with confidentiality." The public can contact Capt Vulikhaya Diniso at 082 441 9918 alternatively the crime stop number:08600 10111. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 